attributes.value: This Course was designed to help you improve 16th-note coordination between your hands and bass drum foot, so your unison strokes become as precise as possible. To do so youll work on playing four rudiments over ten 16th-note bass drum patterns.

This Course was designed to help you improve 8th-note triplet coordination between your hands and bass drum foot, so your unison strokes become as precise as possible. To do so, youll work on playing four rudiments over two bass drum patterns, as well as a challenging five-note pattern exercise that will stretch your independence and time feel.

Hi-hat tricks have been used quite extensively in jazz soloing since the early decades of the genre. From Max Roach to Buddy Rich, to Tom Morello and Steve Smith, pretty much every great jazz drummer has made awesome use of them. So get ready to learn seven legendary hi-hat tricks that will spice up your playing and make your solos much more impressive.

Whether you just bought a Roland TD-50 or are thinking about doing so, this Course will be awesome for you! In it, you'll learn how to set it up, how to create your own kits, how to record your playing, how to change kits and improve your playing with the built in play-alongs and metronome.

Do you struggle with making your drumming more interesting? Do you find yourself playing the same beats and fills over and over again? In that case, this Course is just what you need! In it, JP Bouvet will teach you his five-step system to help you take your creative potential to a completely new level.

Compound rudiments are patterns that are made up of two or more rudiments, and are used quite extensively in the world of Drum Corps. In this Course, Jason Sutter will expose you to nine different compound rudiments and teach you how to play and expand on them. This will improve your overall technique, and most importantly, enable you to build a very unique vocabulary around the drums when you take them to the kit.

If you're a beginner drummer looking for ways to strengthen your weakest hand, this is the Course for you. In it, Issah Contractor will teach you exercises, beats, and fills for strengthening your weakest hand and develop better dynamic and rhythmic control.

This Course is all about improving your jazz independence with the help of Ted Reed's "Syncopation For The Modern Drummer". Besides independence exercises, Gavin Harrison will teach you a concept that you can apply to pretty much anything on the drums to improve your coordination.

This Course continues where the beginner version left off. Issah Contractor will challenge what youve developed so far, with harder patterns that will further your ability. This includes playing ghost notes in succession and after and before accents, rudiments as fills, crashing with the left hand, and incorporating the left hand in hand-to-foot combos.

Beginners usually struggle a lot when it comes to fills and moving around the drum set. With this Course, Julia Geaman will work on this aspect of your drumming with you, by teaching you how to take a single pattern and move it around the kit to work on your mobility and vocabulary.

Developing a good feel behind the drums is a tough thing to do and learn. With that in mind, Josh Dion put together this Course to teach you how you can manipulate your playing in four different ways, to create different feels and start mastering the ability to feel music and play accordingly.

Creating tension is a great way to give your playing layers of depth and up its musical intensity. In this Course, Gabor Dornyei will teach you how to use displacement, five-note groupings, note values, and the dotted 8th-note pulse to achieve just that.

Join Mark Guiliana for this Course, where he'll teach you how to develop your ability to play rhythmic phrases on the kit, with great variety and control. This is an excellent skill to develop if you want to complement the music you're playing to perfectly or want to express yourself on the kit and without shackles.
In this course, Bruce Becker will teach you how to develop your foot technique. He will explore topics like pedal setup, posture, and the fundamentals of the foot.

A follow-up to Bruce Becker's "How To Hold Your Drumsticks" course, this course will examine the motions that can be applied to French, German, American, and Traditional grip. Bruce Becker will also teach you how to apply these motions to the drum-set.

Henrique De Almeida will teach you how to build a Songo groove, some Songo variations, a number of left foot possibilities, and some Songo fills and soloing ideas in this course. There is also a play-along track that is included at the end of the course!
You can learn how to play blast beats from the master himself - Derek Roddy! Traditional blasts, bomb blasts, hammer blasts, and freehand blasts are all covered in this course.
In this course, Aaron Edgar will walk you through a number of different beginner, intermediate, and advanced 5/4 grooves. He'll also teach you five different 5/4 drum fills at the end of the course!

Aaron Edgar will walk you through a number of different beginner, intermediate, and advanced 5/8 beats in this course. At the end of the course, he'll also teach you five different 5/8 drum fills that you can put together with the beats you've learned.

If you have just received your new P4 Practice Pad, be sure to check out this course! Pat Petrillo will explain how to use the pad, how to set it up, and how to care for the pad properly. He will also show you a variety of exercises that you can practice on your P4 Practice Pad.
